        "title": "Governing Authority",
        "text": "Field Value Variable Id pay-governance-paygovauthority Definition The entity or entities responsible for regulatory oversight, rule-setting, licensing, and supervision of the payment system and its participants. Typically includes central bank, financial regulatory authority, telecommunications regulator, or dedicated payment system oversight body. Format Text (400 characters max); \"NA\" if unknown or not applicable Other Metadata Specify primary vs secondary oversight. Note if authority covers prudential regulation, conduct regulation, or both. Indicate if multiple authorities share jurisdiction (e.g., central bank + telecom regulator). Data Collection Guidelines Search: \"[Country] payment system regulation\", \"[Country] central bank payment oversight\", legal framework for payment systems, payment system acts/laws, regulatory authority websites, licensing regimes for payment service providers. For UEMOA/CEMAC member states, also search regional central bank (BCEAO/BEAC) payment system documentation and regional interoperability initiatives.",
